title: For Sale:  Save money and get instant training feedback on how you are shooting with new tracking tool
postcontent: Saw this at SHOT show and was the talk of the range guys. This tool allows you to practice your shooting skills with or without firing any live rounds (also allows you to enter your gun so they get greater accuracy rating). You attach to the rail on your handguns and thru all the sensors it will show you what you are doing wrong or right and how to correct. It allows you to compete with your friends and will keep records of how you have been doing over time. It also has a feature to improve your drawing skills and bringing on target. When you are able to do so proficient at one level it challenges you to improve in less and less time. Overall this is one great way to save money and time (having to load up and go to the range and clean up afterward) by allowing you to train at home and at the drop of a hat.The Targetize Training Sensor is a lightweight 9-axis motion device that attaches to the bottom rail of a handgun, and tracks your muzzle movement as you shoot. The system also measures your acceleration and orientation a thousand of times per second, to pinpoint the difference between your POA (Point of Aim) and where the muzzle was pointing as you made the shot. In addition to providing shooting form tips, Targetize will continuously track the shots you take at every range session and provide scores for your stability, precision, and accuracy. The algorithm its uses was developed with the use of bio-mechanics along with input from shooting instructors and ex-military/special forces. It includes a Targetize sensor, a rail mount, a charging cable, a hard shell case, and a free App. It is compatible with both Android 5 and up, and iOS versions 8 and up.g with input from shooting instructors and ex-military/special forces. Wood stock set has various dents, scratches and marks from wear/use. -19 SA bolt which has the rifles serial number marked into bolt –  rare UNCUT -9 SA flat side op rod, -18 SA trigger housing, -9 SA hammer, SA-11 safety, correct stamped trigger guard for 1945, Lock Bar rear sights, #12 follower, correct stamped bullet guide, WW2 gas lock, gas plug is stamped “P” with an “o”, front sight measures .660” which should be SA.
